---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About · Collaborative Sparks"
  description="Learn about Collaborative Sparks, a living pattern library for healthy collaboration."
>
  <article class="space-y-8 max-w-3xl">
    <header class="space-y-3">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold">What is Collaborative Sparks?</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-sparks-ink/80">
        A living pattern library for healthy collaboration, emerging from real practice in
        regenerative communities, DAOs, cooperatives, and impact networks.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">The Library Structure</h2>
      <p class="text-sparks-ink/80">
        CSparks organizes knowledge into five interconnected content types:
      </p>
      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="bg-white/80 rounded-lg p-4 border border-sparks-amber/20">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-sparks-teal">Patterns</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-sparks-ink/80">
            Reusable solutions to recurring challenges in collaborative life. Patterns describe
            context, problem, forces, and implementation.
          </p>
          <a href="/patterns" class="text-sm text-sparks-teal hover:underline mt-2 inline-block"
            >Browse patterns →</a
          >
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/80 rounded-lg p-4 border border-sparks-amber/20">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-sparks-teal">Forces</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-sparks-ink/80">
            The persistent tensions and dynamics that shape collaborative systems. Forces are not
            problems to solve, but conditions to navigate.
          </p>
          <a href="/forces" class="text-sm text-sparks-teal hover:underline mt-2 inline-block"
            >Explore forces →</a
          >
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/80 rounded-lg p-4 border border-sparks-amber/20">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-sparks-teal">Stories</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-sparks-ink/80">
            Narrative expressions that show patterns and forces in action. Stories provide human
            texture and context.
          </p>
          <a href="/stories" class="text-sm text-sparks-teal hover:underline mt-2 inline-block"
            >Read stories →</a
          >
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/80 rounded-lg p-4 border border-sparks-amber/20">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-sparks-teal">Guides</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-sparks-ink/80">
            Orientation docs and how-to guides that help you navigate the library and learn how to
            engage.
          </p>
          <a href="/guides" class="text-sm text-sparks-teal hover:underline mt-2 inline-block"
            >View guides →</a
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">How to Navigate</h2>
      <p class="text-sparks-ink/80">
        There is no required path through the library. You might browse patterns to discover
        practices that resonate, explore forces to understand underlying tensions, or read stories
        to see how others have navigated similar challenges.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sparks-ink/80">
        The library is designed so you can <em>wander, orient, and return</em>. Follow your
        curiosity.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">A Living Library</h2>
      <p class="text-sparks-ink/80">
        CSparks is not a finished reference. Patterns evolve, new forces are discovered, stories
        accumulate. The library grows through the contributions of practitioners who share what they
        are learning.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sparks-ink/80">
        This approach is inspired by Christopher Alexander's pattern language work, adapted for the
        domain of collaboration. We also draw from Sociocracy 3.0, Teal Organizations, and other
        frameworks for healthy organization.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Get Oriented</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a
          href="/guides/what-is-csparks"
          class="px-4 py-2 bg-sparks-teal text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-sparks-teal/90 transition"
        >
          Read the Introduction
        </a>
        <a
          href="/roles"
          class="px-4 py-2 border border-sparks-teal text-sparks-teal rounded-lg hover:bg-sparks-teal/10 transition"
        >
          Learn About Roles
        </a>
        <a
          href="/contribute"
          class="px-4 py-2 border border-sparks-teal text-sparks-teal rounded-lg hover:bg-sparks-teal/10 transition"
        >
          Ways to Contribute
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t border-sparks-amber/30 pt-6 space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">The Vision</h2>
      <p class="text-sparks-ink/80">
        CSparks is part of a broader vision for healthy collaboration infrastructure. Long-term
        goals include pattern forging tools, contributor pathways, stewardship webrings, and
        integration with decentralized commons infrastructure.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-sparks-ink/60">
        This is just the beginning. Thanks for being part of it.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
